<Layout
  title="Disclosure"
  description="How StackCompass makes money: affiliate disclosure, source-checking process, and how commissions do (and don't) influence recommendations."
  activeNav="disclosure"
  slug="/disclosure/"
  ogType="website"
>
  <h1>Disclosure: How StackCompass Makes Money</h1>

  <div class="lede">
    <p><strong>Disclosure:</strong> Some links on this site are affiliate links. If you sign up through one, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. It never changes what we recommend or the prices you pay.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>What that means in practice</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>When you click a link on this site that goes to an outside marketing tool, it may route through an internal <code>/go/&lt;program&gt;/</code> page and then to that company's affiliate-tracking link.</li>
    <li>If you sign up or purchase after clicking, the vendor may pay us a commission. This does not add anything to your price.</li>
    <li>We do not accept payment in exchange for a specific recommendation, ranking position, or star rating. Commission rate is not the basis for which tool we describe as the best fit for a given reader.</li>
    <li>Some affiliate links on this site are not live yet — see the note below.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Affiliate links that aren't live yet</h2>
  <div class="callout amber">
    <p>Several programs referenced on this site (Systeme.io, GoHighLevel, GetResponse) do not yet have an approved, verified tracking link on file. Rather than invent a placeholder referral link, the internal <code>/go/</code> page for that program currently shows a plain notice that the affiliate link is pending, and links out to nothing but our own homepage. Once a real, verified tracking link is issued, it replaces the placeholder — the outbound link will always carry <code>rel="sponsored nofollow"</code>.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>How figures are sourced</h2>
  <p>Commission rates, cookie windows, and payout terms cited on this site are checked directly against each program's official vendor or network documentation (not third-party roundups) and dated as "verified" on the day they were checked. Figures verified 2026-07-22; re-checked weekly. Affiliate program terms can change without notice — always confirm current terms on the vendor's own affiliate page before making a decision based on commission structure.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not state plan prices as fact unless independently verified; unverified prices are shown as visible "verify before publish" notes rather than invented numbers.</li>
    <li>We do not use first-person "we tested" or "we use this daily" claims about these tools.</li>
    <li>We do not make or imply income guarantees from using or promoting any of these programs.</li>
    <li>We do not bid on any vendor's trademarked terms in paid search, and no vendor trademark appears in this site's domain or brand name.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Disclosure placement on this site</h2>
  <p>A disclosure notice like the one at the top of this page appears at the top of every content page on this site, above the first affiliate call-to-action, and a shorter repeat appears directly next to each affiliate button. This placement follows FTC Endorsement Guide expectations for clear-and-conspicuous disclosure of a material connection.</p>

